  "why": "The paper enforces semantic consistency and naturalness where applicable (notably for discrete inputs) via semantics-preserving mutation functions (EDA for text, SMILES enumeration for molecules) and uses small, parameterized Gaussian perturbations for images/videos. These measures constrain each mutation step to produce valid, realistic variants. However, the mutation loop mutates inputs drawn from the current corpus (Algorithm 1: selecting x from T and applying m(x)), and the paper does not describe any mechanism that bounds cumulative distortion relative to the original seed across many iterations. Thus preservation is effectively applied per mutation step (or relative to the most recent mutant) but the design does not explicitly prevent semantic/naturalness drift accumulating over repeated mutations, matching the \"Medium\" definition.",
